  "text": "The Envoy xDS v3 transport protocol implementation is structured around an adapter pattern with a unified template-based mux system supporting both State-of-the-World (SotW) and Delta modes.\n\n## Core Adapter: GrpcSubscriptionImpl\nThe GrpcSubscriptionImpl class (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h/cc) serves as the main adapter, converting typed Subscription interfaces to untyped GrpcMux operations. It handles per-xDS API stats and logging while managing subscription lifecycle through the GrpcMux interface.\n\n## Legacy Implementation - Two Separate Muxers\nEnvoy initially had two distinct implementations:\n\n1. **SotW Mode (GrpcMuxImpl)**: The legacy State-of-the-World implementation in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc manages subscriptions using full resource snapshots with DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse messages.\n\n2. **Delta Mode (NewGrpcMuxImpl)**: The legacy Delta xDS implementation in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h/cc manages subscriptions with resource-level updates using DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse messages.\n\n## Unified Template Architecture - XdsMux\nTo converge these implementations, Envoy introduced a generic template-based system in the XdsMux namespace (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc):\n\nThe template GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS> is parameterized by:\n- **S**: SubscriptionState type (SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)\n- **F**: SubscriptionStateFactory type (SotwSubscriptionStateFactory or DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory)\n- **RQ**: Request type (DiscoveryRequest or DeltaDiscoveryRequest)\n- **RS**: Response type (DiscoveryResponse or DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n\nTwo concrete specializations are provided:\n- **GrpcMuxSotw**: Specialization for SotW protocol using SotwSubscriptionState\n- **GrpcMuxDelta**: Specialization for Delta protocol using DeltaSubscriptionState\n\n## Subscription State Protocol Handling\nThe xds_mux directory contains abstract and concrete subscription state classes that encapsulate protocol-specific logic:\n\n- **BaseSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h): Abstract template base class handling common protocol concerns like TTL management and response handling.\n\n- **SotwSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/cc): Implements SotW-specific logic including version tracking and full resource snapshot management.\n\n- **DeltaSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/cc): Implements Delta-specific logic including per-resource versioning and incremental updates.\n\n## Configuration Selection - GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory\nThe factory pattern in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc makes the selection between modes:\n\n- **GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory**: Selects between GrpcMuxImpl (legacy) or XdsMux::GrpcMuxSotw (unified) based on the \"envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux\" runtime feature flag.\n\n- **DeltaGrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory**: Selects between NewGrpcMuxImpl (legacy) or XdsMux::GrpcMuxDelta (unified) based on the same runtime feature flag.\n\n- **AdsConfigSubscriptionFactory**: Uses the aggregated discovery service (ADS) mux.\n\nThe factories create GrpcSubscriptionImpl instances wrapping the appropriate mux implementation, enabling runtime switching between the legacy dual-mux approach and the new unified template-based implementation."
}

